    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse the <strong>brown rice</strong>, add it to a large pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p> <p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-glazed-beef-strips-with-pak-choi/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p> <p>Quarter the <strong>chestnut mushrooms&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>Slice the<strong> pak&nbsp;choi&nbsp;</strong>into wedges</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-glazed-beef-strips-with-pak-choi/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over the<strong>&nbsp;highest heat</strong></p> <p>Once very hot, add a splash of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and the<strong> beef strips</strong> and cook for 1-2 min on each side or until they're browned</p> <p>Tip: don't overcook the beef or it will go chewy! If your pan is small, cook it in batches</p> <p>Transfer the <strong>cooked beef strips</strong> to a large plate and set them aside to rest</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-glazed-beef-strips-with-pak-choi/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>Once hot, add the<strong>&nbsp;quartered mushrooms</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to brown</p> <p>Once browned, transfer the <strong>mushrooms</strong> to the plate with the beef strips and return the pan to a low heat</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-glazed-beef-strips-with-pak-choi/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped ginger</strong> to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant&nbsp;</p> <p>Add the<strong> balsamic vinegar</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>honey</strong>,<strong>&nbsp;miso paste</strong>&nbsp;and a splash of <strong>water</strong> and cook for 4-5 min &ndash; this is your <strong>ginger sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-glazed-beef-strips-with-pak-choi/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the <strong>brown rice</strong> is cooked, add the <strong>pak choi halves&nbsp;</strong>to the pot with the<strong> rice</strong>&nbsp;and cook, covered, for a further 3 min or until tender</p> <p>Once done,&nbsp;remove the<strong> pak choi</strong>&nbsp;and set it aside</p> <p>Drain the<strong>&nbsp;brown rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-glazed-beef-strips-with-pak-choi/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, return the <strong>beef strips</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>mushrooms</strong>&nbsp;and any <strong>resting juices</strong> to the <strong>ginger sauce</strong></p> <p>Give everything a good mix up &ndash; this is your <strong>ginger beef</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/ginger-glazed-beef-strips-with-pak-choi/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> pak&nbsp;choi</strong>&nbsp;over the<strong> brown rice</strong> and top with the<strong> ginger beef&nbsp;</strong></p> <p>Garnish with the <strong>fried</strong><strong>&nbsp;onions</strong></p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
